article.headline: Arkansas 95, Alabama A&amp,M 68
article.story: NORTH LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- Marshawn Powell scored 20 points and Arkansas made its first seven field-goal attempts in a 95-68 victory over Alabama A&M on Saturday night. BJ Young added 13 points and Coty Clarke 10 for the Razorbacks (7-4), who had 12 players score and snapped a three-game losing streak at Verizon Arena, its home away from Fayetteville. The Bulldogs (3-7) pulled to within 41-34 late in the first half, but Arkansas scored the final 10 points of the half. The Razorbacks pulled away in the second half, building a lead of 35 points. Demarquelle Tabb scored 15 points for Alabama A&M before fouling out early in the second half.
